Senate President Ahmad Lawan has constituted an ad hoc committee on media and public affairs for the 9th Senate. The committee, headed by Sen Adedayo Adeyeye (APC, Ekiti), is saddled with the responsibility of interfacing with the media pending the setting up of the standing committee. Other members of the ad hoc committee are Aishatu Dahiru (APC, Adamawa), Uba Sani (APC, Kaduna), Abba Moro (PDP, Benue), Ifeanyi Ubah (YPP, Anambra) and Betty Apiafi (PDP, Rivers). OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE Inaugurating the ad hoc committee, yesterday, Lawan tasked the members to ensure that they gave the public proper and correct information about the activities of the Senate. “This committee is necessary because we need the activities of the Senate to be properly and well-articulated and presented to the Nigerian public. This committee will also work and collaborate with our colleagues in the House. “This committee will work pending the proper constitution of the standing committee on media and public affairs. The members of the committee are very experienced,” he said. Lawan also inaugurated the Senate ad hoc committee on legislative agenda, which had Sen. Mohammed Adamu Aliero (APC, Kebbi) as chairman. The committee was given two weeks to conclude its assignment. Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin